This paper discusses the system of categories used in Wikipedia to classify articles, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The paper also analyzes the structural and statistical properties of the category system, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
